@startuml
title Authentication Boundary (Current-State)

skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam DefaultFontName "Arial"

cloud "OAuth Provider" as oauth <<System>>
database "Redis / Session Store" as redis <<System>>
database "PostgreSQL\nidentity schema" as postgres <<System>>
node "Other Services" as internal_clients <<System>>

package "Identity Service" {
  [OAuth Handlers] as oauth_handlers
  [Auth UseCase] as auth_uc
  [JWT Manager] as jwt_mgr
  [Session Manager] as session_mgr
  [User Repository] as user_repo
  [Internal Validate Route] as validate_route
}

oauth_handlers --> auth_uc
auth_uc --> oauth : code exchange / profile fetch
auth_uc --> user_repo
auth_uc --> session_mgr
auth_uc --> jwt_mgr
session_mgr -[#red]> redis : session / blacklist
user_repo -[#green]> postgres : users / jwt_keys / audit_logs
validate_route --> jwt_mgr
internal_clients -[#blue]> validate_route : POST /authentication/internal/validate

note right of auth_uc
Current auth boundary supports:
- OAuth login + callback
- cookie/JWT session
- protected /me and /logout
- internal token validation for service-to-service calls
end note

@enduml
